segments.title: Central Dogma Introduction
segments.summary: Introduces the central dogma of biology which explains how DNA stores and uses genetic information in cells. Discusses how DNA and ribosomes communicate to create proteins.

segments.title: Transcription and Translation Process
segments.summary: Explains how DNA must be transcribed to messenger RNA and then translated by ribosomes to create proteins. This process is key to the central dogma of biology.

segments.title: Summary of Central Dogma
segments.summary: Summarizes that transcription converts DNA to messenger RNA, and translation reads messenger RNA to create proteins in the ribosomes.

segments.title: Quiz on Central Dogma
segments.summary: Presents a quiz question asking students to identify the correct order of processes in the central dogma of biology.
